This paper deals with coding theory, specifically MDS codes, which are a fundamental concept in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial aspects, such as counting the number of codes, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another likely sub-category. The paper may also be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it involves analyzing the complexity of counting MDS codes. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as MDS codes are used in cryptography. Finally, the paper may be relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as it involves analyzing the asymptotic behavior of a formula.
